"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function sns.set_context does not have an rc argument. The rc argument is used in the functions axes_style() and set_style() to customize the seaborn styles. The function sns.set_context is used to set the plotting context parameters. If you want to customize the seaborn styles, you should use the function sns.set_style instead.\", \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< sns.set_context(rc=viz_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_style(rc=viz_dict)\\n\"}"